mplementation is linearizable but not write\nstrongly-linearizable. Finally, we prove that any linearizable implementation\nof SWMR registers is necessarily write strongly-linearizable; this holds for\nshared-memory, message-passing, and hybrid systems.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 26 Feb 2021 00:16:39 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-03-01"}
